title: For Sale:  Remington Nylon 66
postcontent:
I'm selling a Mohawk Brown Nylon 66.  If you don't know about these guns they were the first mass produced rifle that had a stock that wasn't wood.  The receiver and stock are both made of Nylon Zytel-101.  It is semi automatic tube fed where you load the rounds in through the butt of the gun and it's even self lubricating.  This rifles are known to be insanely reliable in any weather conditions and Remington even put a lifetime warranty on all the nylon material from cracking, breaking or even fading because back in those days if it wasn't wood people didn't trust it.  There is a period correct scope mounted on it right now that is somehow still spot on after sitting for quite a while.  The Nylon 66 is known to be very accurate with just the iron sights and even was famous for attaining the aerial shooting record.  It's in good shape with a few scratches that you could buff out if that's what you wanted.  It has just sat inside the house, we did take it out and shoot it the other day and it was flawless and so accurate that we considered keeping it. 
PM all offers and trades.
$300 OBO
